One positive aspect I see right off is the reduction in vibration that
comes with a greater mass.  Since smaller machines tend to transmit
vibrations to the workpiece more readily than larger ones, this alone
would seem to be a benefit.  I once visited a university lab that had
an optical bench, a massive vibrationally isolated and dampened steel
and concrete table to which optical components such as lasers and
special microscopes were attached.  The device was isolated on a
series of hydraulic cylinders, but the assembly was located in the
basement of a large building, mounted on what looked an awful lot like
a giant concrete sarcophagus coming out of the floor.  The principal
investigator of the research project told me that the entire assembly
had been located in the basement prior to the completion of the
building, lowered in by crane.  I can't even imagine what it weighed
(probably on the order of 10 tons or so).
